Hostetler has been charged with a host of offences including resisting 
arrest and second-degree obstructing governmental administration.

He is also charged with unlawful possession of an alcoholic beverage with intent to consume by a person under age 21, reported the Buffalo News.

Three more charges from the incident include failure to yield to an 
emergency vehicle, insufficient tail lamps and littering on a highway.

He was arraigned in Randolph Town Court and taken to jail on $500 bail.

Hostetler will face charges in Conewango Town Court, which is more than 50 miles south of Buffalo, at a later date.

